Describes how the farewell workflow proceeds for the recipient.

Usage: hello-world take-leave [OPTIONS]

Options:
  -c, --config <PATH>
          Path to the configuration file

      --parting <PHRASE>
          Parting phrase to use when saying goodbye
          
          [default: "Take care"]

      --preamble <PHRASE>
          Optional preamble printed before the farewell greeting

      --punctuation <TEXT>
          Optional punctuation override appended to the farewell greeting

      --channel <channel>
          Describes how the farewell follow-up will be delivered

          Possible values:
          - message: Sends a follow-up via instant message
          - call:    Schedules a quick voice call
          - email:   Dispatches a friendly email

      --remind-in <MINUTES>
          Optional reminder delay in minutes

      --gift <ITEM>
          Optional gift noted in the farewell

      --wave
          Records whether the caller waves whilst leaving

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
